      <span class="apn-c-week-label">Week 2: Protocol Locked, Stack Begins</span>
      <p style="margin:0 0 12px 0;font-weight:700;font-size:16px;color:#0D0D0D;">Focus: Gap 1 protocol is now a locked daily behavior. Foundation supplement stack begins.</p>
      <ul class="apn-c-checklist">
        <li>Week 1 protocol continues unchanged. Do not modify it. Let it compound.</li>
        <li>Add Recharge (Creatine, 5g daily) if not already running. Take it at any consistent time. Timing matters less than consistency. Daily creatine loading raises intramuscular phosphocreatine stores by 20 to 25% over two to four weeks, directly improving high-intensity training output.</li>
        <li>Confirm post-training protein: 25g to 30g minimum within 45 minutes. Leucine content matters most. Whey protein naturally delivers 2.5 to 3g leucine per 25g serving, which clears the muscle protein synthesis activation threshold.</li>
        <li>Stack size: two products maximum this week. Foundation before expansion.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="apn-c-assignment">
      <span class="apn-c-assignment-label">Week 2 Assignment</span>
      <p style="margin:0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;">Confirm Recharge is ordered or in hand. Confirm your post-training protein protocol. On Day 14, note whether the Week 1 protocol is now automatic (you don't have to think about it) or still requiring deliberate effort. Automatic means it's consolidating. Deliberate means it needs more time before you layer anything new.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Week 3 -->
    <div class="apn-c-week-block">
      <span class="apn-c-week-label">Week 3: Track the Gap</span>
      <p style="margin:0 0 12px 0;font-weight:700;font-size:16px;color:#0D0D0D;">Focus: Measure Gap 1. Data reveals whether the protocol is working or needs adjustment.</p>
      <ul class="apn-c-checklist">
        <li>If Gap 1 is sleep: track total sleep hours and time in bed for seven consecutive nights. Target: 7.5 to 9 hours. Note how you feel on Day 7 versus Day 1.</li>
        <li>If Gap 1 is nutrition: log protein intake for seven days. Target: 0.7g to 1g per pound of bodyweight, distributed across at least three meals. Note performance and recovery markers.</li>
        <li>If Gap 1 is recovery: track subjective soreness (1 to 10) and training output (weight moved, rounds completed, pace) for seven days. Note any trend.</li>
        <li>Add your gap-targeted third supplement this week based on what your primary gap assessment identified (see Module 5).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="apn-c-assignment">
      <span class="apn-c-assignment-label">Week 3 Assignment</span>
      <p style="margin:0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;">Seven days of tracking. No exceptions. Data is not optional at this tier. At the end of Week 3, answer this question: Is the gap metric improving? Sleep hours up, protein total meeting target, soreness trend down? Yes or no determines Week 4 action.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Scripture -->
    <div class="apn-c-scripture">
      <p>"And let us not grow weary of doing good, for in due season we will reap, if we do not give up."</p>
      <cite>Galatians 6:9</cite>
    </div>

    <!-- Week 4 -->
    <div class="apn-c-week-block">
      <span class="apn-c-week-label">Week 4: Review and Decision</span>
      <p style="margin:0 0 12px 0;font-weight:700;font-size:16px;color:#0D0D0D;">Focus: Assess the gap. Make a data-driven decision. Set Week 5 direction.</p>
      <ul class="apn-c-checklist">
        <li>Review Week 3 tracking data. Is the gap closing measurably?</li>
        <li>If yes: the primary gap is responding. Add one additional element in Week 5: a secondary gap protocol or an additional supplement from the stack. Do not rush. Compound what's working.</li>
        <li>If no: identify what's blocking the protocol. Is the habit not executing (adherence issue)? Is the protocol wrong for the gap (design issue)? Is there a deeper root cause not captured in the initial gap (diagnosis issue)? Fix the blocker before adding anything new.</li>
        <li>Prepare your Week 5 plan before Week 4 ends. Do not leave planning to motivation in the moment.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="apn-c-assignment">
      <span class="apn-c-assignment-label">Week 4 Assignment</span>
      <p style="margin:0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;">Write the answer to two questions before Week 4 ends. First: Is Gap 1 measurably closing? Second: What is the single next action for Week 5? These two answers are your bridge from Competitor to Elite. Bring them to your coaching call if you have one scheduled.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- What next tier requires -->
    <h3 class="apn-c-h3" style="margin-top:40px;">What Elite Requires</h3>
